f=Engineering/ops/operational/agent/ops-config.md · p=Machine-readable configuration ops, production owner. · h2:Config Template=`# --- Charter (senior authority) --- \· security_charter_path: <FILL_IN>      # unadopted → most-restrictive mode (no deploys via external tools) \· escalation_contact: <FILL_IN>         # incidents, failed restores, unpatched criticals → operator \·  \· # --- Release ---` · in=`security_charter_path` most-restrictive mode: external-tool deploys, manual-operator-driven shipping only, stated affected output. Unset `severity_definitions` P0–P3 convention descriptions apply, loudly labeled provisional; propose real definitions after first classification need, during it. Unset cadences/thresholds one initial register-establishing run, proposals operator (labeled reasoning-based) nothing scheduled enforced silently. `critical_flows` resolve source quinn reads divergence between "what quinn gates" "what ops smokes" config finding. Absent connectors detection human-report-driven mechanics manual-per-playbook; stated loudly (incident-response logs contributing factor time). · f=Unfilled config degrades loudly, never silently. charter's absence stops external-tool deploys entirely design, safety net doesn't operate uninsured.